 the organic chair was revolutionary.";i:28;s:120:"Up until this point comfortable chairs were constructed with expensive springs and heavy bolsters of upholstery padding.";i:29;s:55:"The lightweight molded plywood seat was a game changer.";i:30;s:337:"Design Charles Eames Eero Saarinen 1940 Laminate seat shell ash or oak legs upholstery Made in Germany by Vitra For the Organic Design in Home Furnishings competition held by the Museum of Modern Art Charles Eames and Eero Saarinen created an entire series of versions of the Organic chair each intended for a different sitting position.";i:31;s:165:"Kartell has employed a revolutionary material to present a sustainable item of furniture with an industrial background that is both high quality and highly creative.";i:32;s:77:"This so-called Organic Chair is made from BIODURATM a material obtained from.";i:33;s:96:"These lovely and functional organic chair design are available at enticing offers and discounts.";i:34;s:43:"Supernatural chair - Courtesy Moroso Udine.";i:35;s:214:"Inspired by the natural world the Supernatural chair is a superb example of organic essentialist design with its beautiful single-piece single-material construction being informed by cellular forms found in nature.";i:36;s:165:"Solo organic design garden chair is light and slim and is a perfect lounge chair for chilling out in the garden or home and is also a year-round piece of garden art.";i:37;s:31:"Luxury Outdoor Chair Materials.";i:38;s:124:"Back in the 1950s basalt fibre was a Top Secret material used by the Soviet Union in the aerospace industry in the Cold War.";i:39;s:20:"Basalt is light and.";i:40;s:94:"Frank Lloyd Wrights Peacock Chair was designed specifically for Tokyos Imperial Hotel in 1921.";i:41;s:198:"The Peacock Chair features a hexagonal back and geometric shaping in the negative space of the legs reflecting the lines of the famous Peacock Room itself which featured an angular pointed roofline.";i:42;s:100:"Organic interior designs how to create an interior organic space that makes sense and looks perfect.";i:43;s:76:"Organic furniture that can be used in an organic or regular interior design.";i:44;s:89:"Organic pavilions and small buildings that use unusual building materials and techniques.";i:45;s:70:"Organic large buildings where you explode with larger-scale materials.";i:46;s:162:"Chair Designed by Charles Eames and Eero Saarinen for the Organic Design in Home Furnishings Competition designed 1940 molded plywood wood foam rubber and fabric.";i:47;s:25:"Courtesy of Vitra Design.";}}